{"title_page": "Rugal (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Short description|2020 South Korean television series}}\n'''''Rugal'''''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/tag/rugal|title=Rugal|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> ([[Korean language|Korean]]: \ub8e8\uac08; [[Revised Romanization of Korean|RR]]: Lugal) is a 2020 [[Korean drama|South Korean television drama]] directed by Kang Cheol Woo, starring  [[Choi Jin-hyuk]], [[Park Sung-woong]], [[Park Sun-ho]], Jung Hye-in, [[Jo Dong-hyuk]], [[Han Ji-sang|Han Ji Wan]] and Kim Min-sang. ''Rugal'' is based on a [[webtoon]] of the same name by Rilmae<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.naver.com/skylife_blog/221888888525?proxyReferer=|title=\uc2a4\uce74\uc774\ub77c\uc774\ud504 \ube14\ub85c\uadf8\ub77c\uc774\ud504 : \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \ube14\ub85c\uadf8|website=blog.naver.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>, which was first published in October 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1393704wpp/conflicts-deepen-as-rugal-team-sets-off-on-a-new-mission-to-thwart-their-nemesis|title=Conflicts Deepen As \u201cRugal\u201d Team Sets Off On A New Mission To Thwart Their Nemesis|date=1586596171|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.intronews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=406702|title=(OCN \ub8e8\uac08) \uc4f0\ub7ec\uc9c4 \ubc15\uc131\uc6c5! \uce58\uba85\uc801 \uc77c\uaca9 \ub0a0\ub9b0 \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601, \ub9c8\uce68\ub0b4 \ubcf5\uc218 \uc2dc\uc791|date=2020-04-13|website=\uc778\ud2b8\ub85c\ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The first episode series was aired on Mar 28, 2020, on [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN Network]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/202004111005051679|title=\u2018\ub8e8\uac08\u2019 \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601\u2192\uc870\ub3d9\ud601, \ub354 \uac15\ub825\ud574\uc9c4 4\u4eba \ud300\ud50c\ub808\uc774\u2026\uc0c8 \ubbf8\uc158 \ub098\uc120\ub2e4|website=\ud55c\uad6d\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> It was also premiere on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kof.inven.co.kr/dataninfo/fighter/?code=21200|title=\ud0b9 \uc624\ube0c \ud30c\uc774\ud130 \uc62c\uc2a4\ud0c0 \uc778\ubca4 - AS \ubc14\ub2e5\uc744 \ubaa8\ub974\ub294 \uc695\ub9dd\uc758 \ub8e8\uac08|website=kof.inven.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.joins.com/article/23562272|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601\u00b7\ubc15\uc131\uc6c5, OCN '\ub8e8\uac08' \uc8fc\uc778\uacf5|last=\uc785\ub825 2019.08.26 17:31|date=2019-08-26|website=\uc911\uc559\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspim.com/news/view/20200327000787|title='\ub8e8\uac08' '\ucee4\ubba4\ub2c8\ud2f0' '\uc624\uc790\ud06c3'\u2026\ub137\ud50c\ub9ad\uc2a4, \uc774\ubc88\uc8fc \uc2e0\uc791 \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5 \uacf5\uac1c|date=2020-03-27|website=\ub274\uc2a4\ud54c|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Rugal\n| image                    = Rugal poster.jpg\n| caption                  = Promotional poster\n| show_name_2              = \n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|hangul=\ub8e8\uac08}}\n| genre                    = {{ubl|[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]|[[Action film|Action]]|[[Crime]]}}\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = Webtoon by Rilmae\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = Do Hyun\n| director                 = Kang Cheol Woo\n| starring                 = {{ubl|[[Choi Jin-hyuk]]|[[Park Sung-woong]]|[[Park Sun-ho]]|[[Jo Dong-hyuk]]|Jung Hye-in|Kim Min-sang}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = South Korea\n| language                 = Korean\n| num_episodes             = 16\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| camera                   = [[Single-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 60 minutes\n| company                  = {{ubl|[[Studio Dragon]]|LIAN Entertainment}}\n| distributor              = {{ubl|[[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]}}\n| network                  = [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = [[Dolby Digital]]\n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = March 28, 2020\n| last_aired               = \n| preceded_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that preceded another in a television lineup. -->\n| followed_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that followed another in a television lineup. -->\n| related                  = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations -->\n| website                  = http://program.tving.com/ocn/watcher\n}}\n\n== Synopsis ==\nKang Ki-beom ([[Choi Jin-hyuk]]) is an elite police officer whose custody of the Argos, a nationwide criminal organization, results in a group of masked murderers from Argos killing his beloved wife and cutting both eyes. Kang wakes up in a town only to find himself having nothing to do with killing his family members. The NIS approached him as a member of Rugal, an expert team organized by the NIS. He received two artificial eyes with Rugal's biotechnology instructing them and with them unique new studies that would reduce criminal organizations. Kang Ki-beom and Rugal are walking through a life to capture the Argos. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/202004123422I|title='\ub8e8\uac08' \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601 \uc8fd\uc774\uae30 \uc704\ud574 \ub098\ud0c0\ub09c \u2018\uc2e4\ud5d8\uccb4\u2019 \uae40\ub2e4\ud604|date=2020-04-12|website=hankyung.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n\n=== Main ===\n\u2022 [[Choi Jin-hyuk]] as Kang Gi Bum<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/ko-kr/entertainment/tv/%EB%A3%A8%EA%B0%88-%EC%B5%9C%EC%A7%84%ED%98%81-%EB%B0%95%EC%84%B1%EC%9B%85%E3%83%BB%ED%95%9C%EC%A7%80%EC%99%84%EC%97%90-%EC%A0%95%EB%A9%B4-%EB%8F%8C%ED%8C%8C%ED%8D%BC%ED%8E%99%ED%8A%B8-%ED%9E%88%EC%96%B4%EB%A1%9C/ar-BB12uUUX|title='\ub8e8\uac08' \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601, \ubc15\uc131\uc6c5\u30fb\ud55c\uc9c0\uc644\uc5d0 \uc815\uba74 \ub3cc\ud30c..\ud37c\ud399\ud2b8 \ud788\uc5b4\ub85c|website=www.msn.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n\u2022 [[Park Sung-woong]] as Hwang Deuk Goo\n\n\u2022 [[Park Sun-ho]] as Lee Gwang Cheol\n\n\u2022 [[Jung Hae-in|Jung Hye-in]] as Song Mi Na\n\n\u2022 [[Jo Dong-hyuk]] as Han Tae Woong\n\n\u2022 Kim Min-sang as Choi Geun Cheol\n\n\u2022 Han Ji Wan as Choi Ye Won\n\n=== Supporting ===\n\u2022 [[Jang In-sub|Jang In Sub]] as Bradley [Rugal's mechanic]\n\n\u2022 Jang Seo Kyung as Susan [Rugal]\n\n\u2022 Park Choong Seon as Section Chief Oh [Rugal]\n\n\u2022 [[Yoo Sang-joon|Yoo Sang Hoon]] as Min Dal Ho [Argos acting leader]\n\n\u2022 [[Park Jung-hae|Park Jung Hak]] as Go Yong Deok [Assemblyman]\n\n\u2022 [[Kim Jin-woo (musician)|Kim In Woo]] as Choi Yong [Argos]\n\n\u2022 Yoo Ji Yeon as Jang Mi Joo [Argos]\n\n\u2022 Ji Dae Han as Bong Man Cheol [Argos]\n\n\u2022 [[Kim Da-hyun|Kim Da Hyun]] as Seol Min Joon [Argos]\n\n\u2022 [[Lee Do-hyun|Lee Bo Hyun]] as Yang Moon Bok\n\n\u2022 [[Lee Seol|Lee Seo El]] as Yeo Jin [Kang Gi Bum's wife]\n\n\u2022 Dong Hyun Bae as Lee Jae Han\n\n=== Special participation ===\n\u2022 Im Yong Soon as Police (Ep.1)\n\n\u2022 Yoo Hyung Kwan as Goo Won Bong (Ep.1)\n\n\u2022 Kim Yoon Hong as Park No Shik (Ep.1-2)\n\n\u2022 Kim Jong Goo as Politician (Ep. 3)\n\n\u2022 [[Sori (singer)|Kim So Ri]] as Singer\n\n== Production ==\nThe series is directed by Ahn Gil-ho Kang Cheol Woo<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kdramapal.com/first-look-choi-jin-hyuk-park-sung-woong-sci-fi-thriller-rugal/|title=First look at Choi Jin-hyuk, Park Sung-woong in sci-fi thriller 'Rugal'|last=IndoorEnthusiast|date=2020-01-29|website=Kdramapal|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://forums.soompi.com/topic/441992-current-drama-2020-rugal-%EB%A3%A8%EA%B0%88-sat-sun-2250-kst/|title=[Current Drama 2020] Rugal, \ub8e8\uac08 - Sat & Sun @ 22:50 KST|website=Soompi Forums|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> (''The Thousandth Man, Cheo Yong 2: The Paranormal Detective, [[Something About 1%]], [[My Secret Romance]], [[So I Married an Anti-fan (TV series)|So I Married an Anti-Fan]]'')\n\n== Ratings ==\nIn this table, {{color|blue|'''the blue numbers'''}} represent the lowest ratings and {{color|red|'''the red numbers'''}} represent the highest ratings.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"3\" |{{abbr|Ep.|Episode}}\n! rowspan=\"3\" |Original broadcast date\n! colspan=\"2\" |Average audience share\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |AGB Nielsen<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nielsenkorea.co.kr/tv_terrestrial_day.asp?menu=Tit_1&sub_menu=3_1&area=00|title=Nielsen Korea|work=AGB Nielsen Media Research|language=ko|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601140426/http://www.nielsenkorea.co.kr/tv_terrestrial_day.asp?menu=Tit_1&sub_menu=3_1&area=00|archive-date=June 1, 2016|accessdate=July 6, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! width=\"90\" |Nationwide\n! width=\"90\" |[[Seoul Capital Area|Seoul]]\n|-\n!1\n|March 28, 2020\n| -\n|'''{{Color|Red|2.612%}}'''\n|-\n!2\n|March 29, 2020\n| -\n|'''{{Color|Blue|3.884%}}'''\n|-\n!3\n|April 4, 2020\n| -\n|2.874%\n|-\n!4\n|April 5, 2020\n| -\n|3.199%\n|-\n!5\n|April 11, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!6\n|April 12, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!7\n|April 18, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!8\n|April 19, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!9\n|April 25, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!10\n|April 26, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!11\n|May 2, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!12\n|May 3, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!13\n|May 9, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!14\n|May 10, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!15\n|May 16, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n!16\n|May 17, 2020\n| -\n| -\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"